<p><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif width=5><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/headers/current_affairs.gif><center><table width=100%><tr><td background=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/horizon_line.gif><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif height=16></td></tr></table><p><table Border=0 Bgcolor=#181818 Width=100%>
<tr><td colspan=2 Bgcolor=#000000 Align=center><font color=white size=+2>Clerics</font>
</td></tr><tr><td width=10% Bgcolor=#101010 Align=center Valign=top><table width=200><tr><td align=center><font size=-1><table><tr><td align=center><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_top.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_left.jpg><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/portraits/NEKEDHEALER.jpg width="104" height="184"><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_right.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_bottom.jpg></td></tr></table>Legendary  NEKEDHEALER REPLACEROFLIFE<br>Level 61 Cleric<br><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_11.gif" title="Silver Order of Leadership"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_7.gif" title="Star of Achievement"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_16.gif" title="Service Star Cluster"><br>Webmaster<br><a style="text-decoration:none;" href="main.cgi?fetch=NEKEDHEALER"><font size=-1 color="#DDDDDD">NEKEDHEALER</font></a><font size=-1>'S LINEAGE</font><br><img src='http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/bio.gif' border=0></font></td></tr></table></td><td width=90% Valign=top><a href=main.cgi?followup=1&forum=9><p align=right><font color=#cccccc>Reply | </a><a href=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/guild-builder/call/main.cgi?action=messages&forum=9><font color=#cccccc>Return</a></p><br clear=all><p><i>First, those not in the ch rotation need to be healing the MA first and foremost. if the ma dies in the middle of the ch cast, odds are so will tha sa. then we will wipe.<br><br>Second, the ch rotation. if you are called on to be in the rotation, there are a few things you need to know....have a hotkey set up and move it out of the way when not in use. this way when you need it, you don't have to do anything but change the follow name. the hotkey should look like this:<br><br>/cast 2<br>/1 casting CH on %t<br>/cast 2<br>/pause 20<br>/1 Cleric_01 -- cast now<br><br>the cast number should be the number of your ch<br>the reason it is their 2 times is in case of fizzle<br>the pause can be adjusted depending on the mob<br>the /1 will be changed to whatever channel you are using.  Cleric_01 would be whoever is next in line in the rotation<br>in this instance, i would start the ch rotation as soon as "Kruppt" had the mob in front of him, as soon as "Bobbyboy" saw his name in the channel he would hit his hotkey, and so on and so on. if everyone's hotkeys are set up the SAME WAY there should be no confusion about when to cast.<br><br>also, and i learned this tonight at vindi, keep yer ma in range :) if you find you are out of range, just click your ch spell but do not click your hotkey a second time :)<br><br>third, if mod rods are available, use the first charge after your first or second heal. Hopefully, the fight will be over before you can use the next charge, but just in case, you'll recover enough mana for one more heal.<br><br>fourth, fast healing from ch rotation. if we are low on healers, the people at the bottom of ch rotation should fast heal until they see the name for the person ahead of them. example 4 healers, healer 1 starts casting ch, healers 3 and 4 should fast heal, healer 2 starts casting ch, healer 4 should cast fast heal, healer 3 starts casting, healer 4 starts casting. theorically, this should work :)<br><br>finally, have a necro in the channel ready to pump clerics for mana when they get low. and by low i mean 30%. clerics should either say in channel or send a tell -- i suggest have a hotkey ready for this :) -- then again i love hotkeys... :)<br><br>ok if anyone has any suggestions on how to improve this please please please respond to this post.<br><br>--neked<br><br>p.s. on a raid that there is no ch rotation, all healers should be healing the MA...no one else, unless MA is at full health and you are at full mana and heals have not been a problem, this pretty much is not gonna happen. also be sure you have a hotkey set up that tells the RAID (not yer group) that you are healing..whatever heal it is. there is nothing i hate more then ducking out of a heal because someone else just landed one...too many things can and have gone wrong with that....we just need to be sure that healers are communicating with each other.<br><br>i want to thank Renalini for leading me to the link below and for also giving me some good suggestions, which i implemented into this post.  Thanx Rena:)<br><br>also some good information found <A HREF="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&threadid=15364&highlight=Chain" target="_new">here</A><br clear=all></i><br></td></tr><tr><td>
